body:
The check to skip unfocusable/hidden windows in `bufwinnr` seems sus to me. Does this patch fix this for you?

```diff
diff --git a/src/nvim/eval/buffer.c b/src/nvim/eval/buffer.c
index e27f1efa42..299c8e7889 100644
--- a/src/nvim/eval/buffer.c
+++ b/src/nvim/eval/buffer.c
@@ -381,6 +381,9 @@ static void buf_win_common(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv, bool get_nr)
   bool found_buf = false;
   FOR_ALL_WINDOWS_IN_TAB(wp, curtab) {
     winnr += win_has_winnr(wp);
+    if (get_nr && !win_has_winnr(wp)) {
+      continue;
+    }
     if (wp->w_buffer == buf) {
       found_buf = true;
       winid = wp->handle;
```

(I think what's happening is `BufWinLeave` is firing for the float's buffer, but `bufwinnr()` is giving the window number of the diff window instead)
